#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:876
#, no-c-format
msgid "Administrator's Guide"
msgstr "Vodnik za skrbnike"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:879
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compatibility Issues"
msgstr "Težave z združljivostjo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:881
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section provides help with how to make &kontact; communicate "
"effectively with various groupware solutions."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek ponuja pomoč pri ustvarjanju &kontact; učinkovito komunicirati z "
"različnimi rešitvami za skupinsko programsko opremo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:887
#, no-c-format
msgid "Outlook and Exchange"
msgstr "Outlook in Exchange"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:889
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the &kontact; configuration dialog, under <menuchoice><guimenu>Mail</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Misc</guimenuitem></menuchoice> on the "
"<guilabel>Invitations</guilabel> page you will find the following options "
"that will help the user communicate with Microsoft Outlook(tm) running in a "
"Kolab environment or in a Microsoft Exchange(tm) environment."
msgstr ""
"V &kontact; konfiguracijsko pogovorno okno, boste pod "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Pošta</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Razno</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> na strani <guilabel>Vabila</guilabel> našli naslednje možnosti, "
"ki bodo uporabniku pomagale komunicirati z Microsoft Outlook(tm), ki se "
"izvaja v okolju Kolab ali v okolju Microsoft Exchange(tm)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:900
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mangle From:/To: headers in replies to invitations"
msgstr "Mangle od:/do: glave v odgovorih na povabila"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:902
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enable this option to make Microsoft Outlook(tm) understand your answers to "
"invitation replies."
msgstr ""
"Omogočite to možnost, da bo Microsoft Outlook(tm) razumel vaše odgovore na "
"odgovore na povabila."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Microsoft Outlook has a number of shortcomings in its implementation of the "
"iCalendar standard; this option works around one of them. If you have "
"problems with Outlook users not being able to get your replies, try setting "
"this option."
msgstr ""
"Microsoft Outlook ima številne pomanjkljivosti pri izvajanju standarda "
"iCalendar; ta možnost deluje okoli enega od njih. Če imate težave z "
"uporabniki Outlooka, ki ne morejo dobiti vaših odgovorov, poskusite "
"nastaviti to možnost."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:907
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Details: When mailing an iCal invitation this makes the message have the "
"From: header the same as the To: header. It also sets header X-KMail-"
"Identity to the To:'s UIOD and makes sure the BCC: is blank. Outlook will "
"only understand the reply if the From: header is the same as the To: header "
"of the invitation message."
msgstr ""
"Podrobnosti: Ko pošiljate povabilo iCal, ima to sporočilo glavo Od: enako "
"kot glavo Za:. Prav tako nastavi glavo X-KMail-Identity na UIOD Za: in "
"poskrbi, da je BCC: prazno. Outlook bo odgovor razumel le, če je glava Od: "
"enaka glavi Za: v vabilu."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:916
#, no-c-format
msgid "Send invitations in the mail body"
msgstr "Pošlji vabila v telesu pošte"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:918
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Invitations are normally sent as attachments to a mail. This switch changes "
"the invitation to be sent in the text of the mail instead; this is necessary "
"to send invitations and replies to Microsoft Outlook. But, when you do this, "
"you no longer get descriptive text that mail programs can read; so, to "
"people who have email programs that do not understand the invitations, the "
"resulting messages look very odd. People that have email programs that do "
"understand invitations will still be able to work with this."
msgstr ""
"Vabila so običajno poslana kot priponke k e-pošti. To stikalo spremeni "
"vabilo, ki bo namesto tega poslano v besedilu pošte; to je potrebno za "
"pošiljanje povabil in odgovorov v Microsoft Outlook. Toda ko to storite, ne "
"dobite več opisnega besedila, ki bi ga poštni programi lahko prebrali; tako "
"so za ljudi, ki imajo e-poštne programe, ki ne razumejo povabil, nastala "
"sporočila videti zelo čudna. Ljudje, ki imajo e-poštne programe, ki razumejo "
"povabila, bodo še vedno lahko delali s tem."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:926
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Details: When mailing an iCal invitation this option makes the message body "
"from the attachment data and sets the Content-Type header to 'text/calendar; "
"method=something; charset=\"utf-8\"'."
msgstr ""
"Podrobnosti: pri pošiljanju povabila iCal ta možnost ustvari telo sporočila "
"iz podatkov priloge in nastavi glavo Content-Type na 'text/calendar; "
"metoda=nekaj; charset=\"utf-8\"'."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:929
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Auto-sending is also turned on so there is no human intervention required "
"for composing."
msgstr ""
"Vklopljeno je tudi samodejno pošiljanje, tako da za sestavljanje ni potreben "
"človeški poseg."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:931
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encryption and self-signing are disabled."
msgstr "Šifriranje in samopodpisovanje sta onemogočena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:936
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exchange-compatible invitation naming"
msgstr "Poimenovanje povabila, združljivo z Exchange"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:938
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Microsoft Outlook, when used in combination with a Microsoft Exchange(tm) "
"server, has a problem understanding standards-compliant groupware email. "
"Enable this option to send groupware invitations in a way that Microsoft "
"Exchange(tm) understands. The invitation will be sent as an attachment with "
"name <filename>ical.ics</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Microsoft Outlook, če se uporablja v kombinaciji s strežnikom Microsoft "
"Exchange(tm), ima težave pri razumevanju e-pošte skupinske programske "
"opreme, skladne s standardi. Omogočite to možnost, če želite poslati "
"povabila skupinski programi na način, ki ga Microsoft Exchange(tm) razume. "
"Povabilo bo poslano kot priponka z imenom <filename>ical.ics</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:943
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Details: When mailing an iCal invitation this makes the message have the "
"subject \"(Declined|Tentative|Accepted|Delegated): subject\". The invitation "
"will be sent as an attachment with name <filename>ical.ics</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Podrobnosti: Ko pošljete povabilo iCal, ima to sporočilo zadevo \"(Zavrnjeno|"
"Pogojno|Sprejeto|Delegirano): zadeva\". Povabilo bo poslano kot priponka z "
"imenom <filename>ical.ics</filename>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:950
#, no-c-format
msgid "Outlook-compatible attachment naming"
msgstr "Poimenovanje prilog, združljivo z Outlookom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:952
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Turn this option on to make Outlook(tm) understand attachment names "
"containing non-English characters."
msgstr ""
"Vklopite to možnost, da bo Outlook(tm) razumel imena prilog, ki vsebujejo "
"neangleške znake."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:964
#, no-c-format
msgid "Behavioral Issues"
msgstr "Vedenjske težave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:966
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section provides instructions on how to make &kontact; behave more like "
"other groupware clients."
msgstr ""
"V tem razdelku so navodila, kako narediti &kontact; se obnašajo bolj kot "
"drugi odjemalci skupinskega programa."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:972
#, no-c-format
msgid "Composing Messages"
msgstr "Sestavljanje sporočil"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:974
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Outlook users are accustomed to typing a list of addresses in the To:, CC: "
"or BCC: fields separated by a semicolon (';') character in addition to a "
"comma (','). By default, &kontact; only allows the comma as an address "
"separator character. To also allow the semicolon, change the "
"<option>AllowSemicolonAsAddressSeparator</option> from false to true in the "
"installed <filename>share/config.kcfg/messagecomposer.kcfg</filename> file."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniki Outlooka so navajeni, da v polja Za:, CC: ali BCC: vnesejo seznam "
"naslovov, ločenih s podpičjem (';') poleg vejice (','). Privzeto &kontact; "
"dovoljuje samo vejico kot znak za ločevanje naslovov. Če želite dovoliti "
"tudi podpičje, spremenite <option>AllowSemicolonAsAddressSeparator</option> "
"iz false v true v nameščeni datoteki <filename>share/config.kcfg/"
"messagecomposer.kcfg</filename>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:988
#, no-c-format
msgid "RFC Compromises"
msgstr "Kompromisi RFC"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:990
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kontact; is designed to interoperate as well as is possible with a wide "
"variety of groupware solutions. To that end, we sometimes make design "
"compromises with respect to the various Internet RFCs that provide the basis "
"for low-level libraries on which &kontact; relies heavily."
msgstr ""
"&kontact; je zasnovan za medsebojno delovanje, kolikor je le mogoče, s "
"široko paleto rešitev skupinskega programja. V ta namen včasih sklepamo "
"kompromise v zvezi z različnimi internetnimi RFC-ji, ki zagotavljajo osnovo "
"za nizkonivojske knjižnice, na katerih &kontact; se močno zanaša."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:996
#, no-c-format
msgid "We never knowingly violate any RFC."
msgstr "Nikoli zavestno ne kršimo nobenega RFC."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:998
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following list of RFC compromises is made by &kontact; or the low-levels "
"libraries used by &kontact;:"
msgstr ""
"Naslednji seznam kompromisov RFC je pripravil &kontact; ali nizkonivojske "
"knjižnice, ki jih uporablja &kontact;:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1003
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When writing duration values into iCalendar files, &kontact; never writes "
"the DURATION property in terms of weeks (i.e., 1*DIGIT \"W\"); instead, the "
"integer number of weeks is always multiplied by 7 and written in terms of "
"days (i.e. 1*DIGIT \"D\")."
msgstr ""
"Ko zapisujete vrednosti trajanja v datoteke iCalendar, &kontact; lastnosti "
"TRAJANJE nikoli ne zapiše v tednih (tj. 1*ŠTEVKA \"W\"); namesto tega je "
"celo število tednov vedno pomnoženo s 7 in zapisano v dnevih (tj. 1*ŠTEVKA "
"\"D\")."

